      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. so when people say the growth will \"benefit everyone,\" is there actually much empirical evidence to support that, or is it mostly just supply-side theory? i'm seeing a lot of conflicting data on whether those trickle-down effects actually materialize in modern economies.",
      "source": "evaluator"
