      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"trickle-down\" argument is fundamentally rooted in supply-side theory, which posits that tax reductions spur investment that eventually benefits all economic strata. However, empirical evidence in modern economies consistently shows that the benefits of such policies are highly concentrated at the top. Instead of broad-based benefits, the data often reflects increased capital accumulation for the wealthiest individuals, leading to persistent inequality.",
